<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08312</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING DULY APPOINTED JUDGES OF THE METROPOLITAN TRIAL COURT AN INCENTIVE REMUNERATION, HEREIN KNOWN AS HAZARD PAY, EQUIVALENT TO AT LEAST TWENTY PERCENT (20%) OF THEIR BASIC MONTHLY SALARY, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to grant hazard pay without tax to Judges of the Metropolitan Trial Court in recognition of their hard work and prompt action on criminal cases that need to be resolved.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-27</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-11-19)</td><td>2. Malapitan (000 2018-11-27)</td><tr><td>3. Sandoval (000 2018-11-29)</td><td>4. Olivarez (000 2018-12-04)</td><tr><td>5. Martinez (000 2018-12-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE ON 2018-10-02</td></tr></table>